 ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Pabenham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Pakenham (Suffolk). The placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Pacca</i> (genitive <i>Paccan</i>) + <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’.","History: A family of this name has been established in Westmeath, Ireland, since the 16th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":15,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":28,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":37,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Pabenham was born about 1300, in Bedfordshire, England, his father, John de Pabenham High Sheriff, was 11298 and his mother, Elizabeth Clifford, was 21. He married Alice de Ufford about 1333, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 18 September 1344, in his hometown, at the age of 45."},"et":{"about 1300–18 September 1344":"umbes 1300–18. september 1344","1300–1344":"1300–1344","1310–1370":"1310–1370","1334–1399":"1334–1399","1248–1322":"1248–1322","1280–1345":"1280–1345","1370":"1370","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1248":"1248","Abt 1333":"umbes 1333","1345":"1345","1334":"1334","1322":"1322","1399":"1399","1344":"1344","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","about 1334":"umbes 1334","about 1300":"umbes 1300","1 December 1322":"1. detsember 1322","18 September 1344":"18. september 1344","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Fen Drayton, Cambridgeshire, England":"Fen Drayton, Cambridgeshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1300–18 September 1344":"noin 1300–18. syyskuuta 1344","1300–1344":"1300–1344","1310–1370":"1310–1370","1334–1399":"1334–1399","1248–1322":"1248–1322","1280–1345":"1280–1345","1370":"1370","1280":"1280","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1248":"1248","Abt 1333":"noin 1333","1345":"1345","1334":"1334","1322":"1322","1399":"1399","1344":"1344","1300":"1300","1453":"1453","1310":"1310","about 1334":"noin 1334","about 1300":"noin 1300","1 December 1322":"1. joulukuuta 1322","18 September 1344":"18. syyskuuta 1344","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Fen Drayton, Cambridgeshire, England":"Fen Drayton, Cambridgeshire, England","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1300–18 September 1344":"environ 1300–18 septembre 1344","1300–1344":"1300–1344","1310–1370":"1310–1370","1334–1399":"1334–1399","1248–1322":